sentences: Julia Clifford (19 June 1914 – 18 June 1997) was a fiddler and Irish traditional musician.
In the late Thirties she emigrated to Scotland and then to London where she worked as a hotel maid before marrying John Clifford in 1941.
In the late Thirties she emigrated to Scotland and then to London where she worked as a hotel maid before marrying John Clifford in 1941.
In the Forties they played the Irish dance halls in London.
In the 1950s they returned to Ireland for a time, living in Newcastle West in Co Limerick.
In 1968 Claddagh recorded herself and brother Denis Murphy on an album of Kerry music, The Star Above the Garter.
Rediscovered by the British folk club scene of the Seventies, Topic in 1977 issued an earlier recording of herself with brother Denis and Padraig O'Keeffe, Kerry Fiddles (Music from Sliabh Luachra).
Her husband John died in 1981.
Julia Clifford died on June 18, 1997, one day before her 84th birthday, and is buried in Norfolk.
